</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Information_rights_arm  Entity: Information_usage_right_relationship  
   <express_ref linkend="information_rights:arm:Information_rights_arm.Information_usage_right_relationship"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Information_rights_arm.Information_usage_right_relationship">
An <b>Information_usage_right_relationship</b> is the relationship of one <express_ref linkend="information_rights:arm:Information_rights_arm.Information_usage_right"/> to another.
<example> Where one <express_ref linkend="information_rights:arm:Information_rights_arm.Information_usage_right"/> supercedes another, then the original right is pointed to by the <b>relating</b>
attribute, its replacement by the <b>related</b> attribute, and the <b>relation_type</b> attribute takes the value "supercedes".</example>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Information_rights_arm  Entity: Information_usage_right_relationship  Attribute: related 
   <express_ref linkend="information_rights:arm:Information_rights_arm.Information_usage_right_relationship.related"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Information_rights_arm.Information_usage_right_relationship.related">
the other instance of <express_ref linkend="information_rights:arm:Information_rights_arm.Information_usage_right">Information_usage_rights</express_ref> that is a part of the relationship. If one <express_ref linkend="information_rights:arm:Information_rights_arm.Information_usage_right"/> participating in the relationship is dependent upon the other, this attribute shall be the dependent one. 
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Information_rights_arm  Entity: Information_usage_right_relationship  Attribute: relating 
   <express_ref linkend="information_rights:arm:Information_rights_arm.Information_usage_right_relationship.relating"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Information_rights_arm.Information_usage_right_relationship.relating">
one of the  instances of <express_ref linkend="information_rights:arm:Information_rights_arm.Information_usage_right"/> that is a part of  the relationship.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Information_rights_arm  Entity: Information_usage_right_relationship  Attribute:relation_type 
   <express_ref linkend="information_rights:arm:Information_rights_arm.Information_usage_right_relationship.relation_type"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Information_rights_arm.Information_usage_right_relationship.relation_type">
a role that defines the behaviour of the relationship.
	</ext_description>
